    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const orgDoc = $('Find Org by Phone').first().json;\nconst orgName = orgDoc.name || 'Organization';\nconst triggerData = $('Execute Workflow Trigger').first().json;\nconst userInput = triggerData.userInput;\nconst phoneNumber = triggerData.phoneNumber;\nconst userIntent = orgDoc.userIntent;\n\n// Get previously collected fields from session\nconst session = $('Fetch Registration Session').first().json;\nlet previousFields = {};\nif (session && session.collectedFields) {\n  try {\n    previousFields = typeof session.collectedFields === 'string'\n      ? JSON.parse(session.collectedFields)\n      : session.collectedFields;\n  } catch(e) {\n    previousFields = {};\n  }\n}\n\nfunction buildParameterGuide(parameters) {\n  if (!parameters || parameters.length === 0) return \"  No parameters.\";\n  return parameters.map(p => {\n    let line = `  - PARAMETER_NAME_COPY_EXACTLY=\"${p.name}\" | Type: ${p.type} | resolvedBy: ${p.resolvedBy}`;\n    if (p.description) line += ` | Description: ${p.description}`;\n    if (p.options) line += ` | Valid options: ${p.options.join(\", \")}`;\n    return line;\n  }).join(\"\\n\");\n}\n\nconst paramGuide = buildParameterGuide(userIntent.parameters);\nconst previousFieldsJson = JSON.stringify(previousFields);\n\nconst prompt = `\nORGANISATION: ${orgName}\nUSER PHONE NUMBER: ${phoneNumber}\nUSER MESSAGE: ${userInput}\n\nPREVIOUSLY COLLECTED FIELDS:\n${previousFieldsJson}\n\nUSER INTENT PARAMETERS:\n${paramGuide}\n`;\n\nreturn [{ json: { prompt } }];"
      },
      "id": "2f21b188-199f-4f60-b5cb-fb89c588bc6a",
      "name": "Build User Intent Prompt",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        -880,
        160
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "={{ $json.prompt }}",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are a friendly WhatsApp onboarding assistant.\n\nYOUR TASK:\nCollect user information for registration based on the USER INTENT PARAMETERS provided in each message.\n\n---\n\nSTEP 1 - RECOVER STATE (CRITICAL):\nRead the PREVIOUSLY COLLECTED FIELDS from the input.\nEvery field already present there is CONFIRMED — carry it forward unchanged into collectedData.fields.\nNever re-ask for or drop a confirmed field.\n\n---\n\nSTEP 2 - PROCESS PARAMETERS:\n\nFIELD NAMING — NON-NEGOTIABLE:\nThe key in collectedData.fields MUST be copied character-for-character from the name property of that parameter. It is case-sensitive.\n\nFor each parameter, read its resolvedBy property:\n\nresolvedBy = \"user\"\n  Must come from the user message or PREVIOUSLY COLLECTED FIELDS.\n  If not found in either -> missing. Ask naturally in STEP 4.\n  FOLLOW-UP OVERRIDE: If already asked once and user replied with anything relevant -> accept immediately.\n\nresolvedBy = \"auto\"\n  Generate the value yourself. Always produce a value. Never missing.\n\nresolvedBy = \"infer\"\n  Use the description and available context (like USER PHONE NUMBER) to determine the value silently.\n  Always produce a value. Never ask the user.\n\nOnly resolvedBy = \"user\" parameters can ever be missing.\n\n---\n\nSTEP 3 - SMART EXTRACTION:\nScan the user message for ALL relevant information at once.\nIf the message contains multiple pieces of data (e.g. \"my name is Akshay and email is abc@gmail.com\"), extract ALL matching parameters in one go.\nDo not ask for a field that is already present in the user message.\n\n---\n\nSTEP 4 - DECIDE:\n\nIf PREVIOUSLY COLLECTED FIELDS is empty or {} (first interaction):\n  Greet warmly using the ORGANISATION name.\n  Ask naturally for all missing resolvedBy=\"user\" fields.\n  Do NOT use technical parameter names — ask like a human support agent.\n\nIf user message does not contain any relevant registration data AND there are still missing fields:\n  Respond politely: \"Sorry, I didn't quite get that. Could you please provide [missing info] to continue the registration?\"\n\nIf all resolvedBy = \"user\" parameters are collected (from previous + current):\n  allCollected = true\n  Confirm briefly (e.g. \"Thanks, got it!\").\n\nIf any resolvedBy = \"user\" parameter is still missing:\n  allCollected = false\n  Acknowledge what you received and ask for the remaining fields naturally.\n\n---\n\nCRITICAL: collectedData.fields must ALWAYS contain ALL parameters — the previously collected ones, the newly collected ones, AND the auto/infer resolved ones. Never return a partial set.\n\nReturn valid JSON only. No markdown. No code fences.\n\n{\n  \"allCollected\": true_or_false,\n  \"collectedData\": {\n    \"fields\": {}\n  },\n  \"message\": \"message to send to user\"\n}"
        }
      },
